article.headline: Hill scores 31, Bowling Green downs Toledo 76-68

images.name: Rashaun Agee gets rebound and slam for Bowling Green
images.caption: Rashaun Agee gets rebound and slam for Bowling Green

article.linkText: Hill scores 31, Bowling Green downs Toledo 76-68
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- — Marcus Hill scored 31 points as Bowling Green beat Toledo 76-68 on Friday night. Hill added six rebounds for the Falcons (17-10, 8-6 Mid-American Conference). Da'Shawn Phillip scored 11 points while shooting 4 for 7, including 1 for 4 from beyond the arc, and added six rebounds. Rashaun Agee finished 4 of 8 from the floor to finish with 10 points. The Rockets (17-10, 11-3) were led in scoring by Ra'Heim Moss, who finished with 19 points and three steals. Tyler Cochran added 17 points and seven rebounds for Toledo. In addition, Dante Maddox Jr. finished with 15 points. Bowling Green took the lead with 1:43 remaining in the first half and did not give it up. Hill led their team in scoring with 16 points in the first half to help put them ahead 39-38 at the break. Hill's 15-point second half helped Bowling Green finish off the eight-point victory. These two teams both play Tuesday. Bowling Green hosts Miami (OH) and Toledo hosts Northern Illinois. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
